## Third-Party Database Licenses

MetaboGraph integrates data from the following databases, each with their own licensing terms:

### HMDB (Human Metabolome Database)
- Website: https://hmdb.ca
- License: Free for academic and non-commercial use
- Citation Required: Yes
- Terms: https://hmdb.ca/about#citing

### LipidMaps (LIPID MAPS Structure Database)
- Website: https://lipidmaps.org
- License: Free for academic use
- Citation Required: Yes
- Terms: https://lipidmaps.org/about/citing

### PathBank
- Website: https://pathbank.org
- License: Open access for academic use
- Citation Required: Yes
- Terms: https://pathbank.org/citing

### SMPDB (Small Molecule Pathway Database)
- Website: https://smpdb.ca
- License: Free for academic and non-commercial use
- Citation Required: Yes
- Terms: https://smpdb.ca/about#citing

### WikiPathways
- Website: https://wikipathways.org
- License: Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 Unported (CC BY 3.0)
- Citation Required: Yes
- Terms: https://www.wikipathways.org/help.html

### PubChem
- Website: https://pubchem.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov
- License: Public Domain (U.S. Government work)
- Citation: Optional but recommended
- Terms: https://pubchem.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/docs/programmatic-access

### KEGG (Kyoto Encyclopedia of Genes and Genomes)
- Website: https://www.kegg.jp
- License: Free for academic use; commercial license required for commercial use
- Citation Required: Yes
- Terms: https://www.kegg.jp/kegg/legal.html

### Reactome
- Website: https://reactome.org
- License: Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
- Citation Required: Yes
- Terms: https://reactome.org/license

## Python Dependencies

See requirements.txt for full list of Python packages and their licenses:
- Most are BSD, MIT, or Apache 2.0 licensed
- Some scientific packages use their own permissive licenses
- Check individual package licenses before commercial use

## Commercial Use

For commercial use of MetaboGraph:
1. MetaboGraph software itself: MIT License (permitted)
2. Third-party databases: Check individual database terms
3. Some databases require commercial licenses for commercial applications
4. Contact database providers for commercial licensing options

